frameDefinitions: A specified Designer or a Brand creates and distributes a Collection of related Products.
This frame has to do with scientific taxonomy.
A Cognizer takes a certain Expectation to be a reliable fact, such that their plans can be based on it.
A Group is described as having members which are similar or dissimilar to each other.
This frame has to do with nouns denoting types of entities.
This frame contains nouns denoting Aggregates of Individuals.
frameExamples: The new Gucci <t>line</t> is due out in early Spring.
<t><fex name='Rank'>Phylum</fex></t> Arthropoda contains crustaceans, insects, spiders and other creepy-crawlies.

listRoleDefinitions: The company that produces the <fen>Collection</fen> of <fen>Products</fen>.
The set of <fen>Products</fen> produced by the <fen>Brand</fen>.
The individual items produced by the <fen>Brand</fen>.
The <fen>Rank</fen> is the taxonomic category to which the <fen>Member</fen> belongs.  It is also always the target-denoting noun.
The living organism which belongs to the expressed <fen>Rank</fen>.
An individual that considers the Expectation certain.
The fact which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> depends on in planning for the future.
This role marks constituents that express the set of objects or types whose diversity is at issue.
This role marks constituents which express a property in respect to which the similarity of the <fen>Group</fen> is assessed.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the Group is diverse or homogenous.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the general area in which diversity occurs or exists.
The entity which denotes a subtype of the more general <fen>Category</fen>.
The more general type that the target denotes a subtype of. This role is obligatory and should be labeled DNI when not present.
This role identifies the people or things that form  the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
This role identifies the collection of entities that are the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
